data.description: Stop the car for this beautifully maintained Beverly bungalow, located on a street off the beaten path with plenty of beautiful trees, greenscapes, and flowers. As you enter the main entrance off of the side driveway, floor one boasts 3 sizable first-floor bedrooms, a cedar entryway closet, and a sun-drenched living room perfect for those early morning tea/coffee breaks all tied together by a beautifully maintained cocoa wooden floor. As you invite yourself into the remaining areas on the first floor, you experience an expansive porcelain tiled kitchen connected to the spacious dining room offering an open-floor concept. Your eyes will be immediately drawn to the beautiful cabinets and backsplash while you enjoy your favorite meal.  The sizable island provides additional counter space for entertaining/meal prep along with a nearby built-in coffee/tea bar. Adjacent to the kitchen/dining area near the rear entrance to the home is a mudroom-inspired space convenient for shoes, coats, and other miscellaneous household items.  Next to the tea/coffee bar, you will find a staircase leading to the 2nd floor, which has been repurposed as the owner's suite. This floor provides exclusive privacy for the owner, fully equipped with recessed sleeping space for added serenity, a separate bedroom-sized custom built-in closet, and an added space ideal for a home office.   The fully finished basement has been equipped with drain tile, a waterproof membrane, a sewer line check valve, and two sump pumps. The entertainment space encompasses the center of the middle of the basement and ties in the additional lower-level areas, which include a bedroom, wet bar, full bath (with an exceptionally large shower), laundry room, and a mechanics room tucked away from normal view/access.    Exit from the basement door to the rear of the home and get blown away by the 2-car garage with driveway and alley access. The side driveway makes it easy for you and your guests to park without a hassle. There is also plenty of street parking for friends and family.  This low-maintenance bungalow is equipped with a newer roof, central air unit, furnace, HW tank,  windows, as well as copper piping, providing you with peace of mind that the home has been well-maintained.   Located in a walk-friendly neighborhood, this home is centrally located near shops, entertainment, and local dining. To put it simply, if you're looking for a beautiful, well-maintained home in a great location, then this Beverly Bungalow is perfect for you.
